   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Richmond Community Centre</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Richmond is a small Karoo town in the northern cape.  This project started as a soup kitchen feeding children in the community as the unemployment rate is about 85%. Due to unemployment, poverty faces many children daily in Richmond.  With the support of individual donors and strong community leaders, we are able to feed over 200 daily. The Community Centre has become a safe space for many children to be themselves and to take part in the educational activities the organization had to offer.</narrative>
  </description>
